parameters.description: Maximum phytoplankton growth rate at reference temperature
parameters.enhanced_semantic_description: Maximum phytoplankton intrinsic growth rate at reference temperature T_ref (day^-1); infrastructure in place for temperature modulation via Q10 when temperature data becomes available

parameters.description: Half-saturation constant for nutrient uptake by phytoplankton
parameters.enhanced_semantic_description: Half-saturation nutrient concentration for phytoplankton uptake (g C m^-3)

parameters.description: Nutrient uptake efficiency (logit-transformed, will be bounded 0-1)
parameters.enhanced_semantic_description: Phytoplankton nutrient uptake efficiency (proportion 0-1); logit value of 0.8 transforms to ~0.69 (69% efficiency), consistent with marine phytoplankton carbon conversion efficiency

parameters.description: Maximum zooplankton grazing rate at reference temperature
parameters.enhanced_semantic_description: Maximum zooplankton grazing rate on phytoplankton at reference temperature T_ref (day^-1); infrastructure in place for temperature modulation via Q10 when temperature data becomes available

parameters.description: Half-saturation constant for zooplankton grazing on phytoplankton
parameters.enhanced_semantic_description: Half-saturation phytoplankton concentration for zooplankton grazing (g C m^-3)

parameters.description: Zooplankton assimilation efficiency (logit-transformed, will be bounded 0-1)
parameters.enhanced_semantic_description: Zooplankton assimilation efficiency of ingested phytoplankton (0-1); logit value of -0.4 transforms to ~0.40 (40% efficiency), consistent with marine zooplankton growth efficiency

parameters.description: Phytoplankton mortality rate at reference temperature
parameters.enhanced_semantic_description: Phytoplankton natural mortality rate at reference temperature T_ref (day^-1); infrastructure in place for temperature modulation via Q10 when temperature data becomes available

parameters.description: Zooplankton mortality rate at reference temperature
parameters.enhanced_semantic_description: Zooplankton natural mortality rate at reference temperature T_ref (day^-1); infrastructure in place for temperature modulation via Q10 when temperature data becomes available

parameters.description: Nutrient recycling fraction from dead organic matter (logit-transformed, will be bounded 0-1)
parameters.enhanced_semantic_description: Fraction of dead biomass recycled to nutrients (0-1); logit value of 0.0 transforms to 0.50 (50% recycling), middle of typical range 30-80%

parameters.description: Temperature sensitivity coefficient - factor by which biological rates increase per 10°C temperature increase
parameters.enhanced_semantic_description: Q10 temperature coefficient for metabolic rate scaling (dimensionless); typical values for marine plankton range 1.5-3.0, with 2.0 representing a doubling of rates per 10°C increase; currently not actively modulating rates (awaiting temperature data), but infrastructure is in place
Reference temperature at which base rates (r_P, g_max, m_P, m_Z) are defined (°C); currently serves as assumed constant temperature; typical range 15-20°C for temperate marine systems
